                                                                                                                                           \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"2160\" height=\"1215\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Pixel Watch 2 on wrist \" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/copy-of-169-10.png\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGoogle really got a lot of things right with the Pixel Watch 2, delivering an experience that many people were looking for when the brand released its first smartwatch. While not much changed when it came to the looks, the Pixel Watch 2 really made some big changes when it came to battery life, delivering true all-day use without any compromises. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eYou also get excellent health and fitness tracking, along with access to a wide variety of apps for wearables thanks to Wear OS. The good news is that Google will continue to support this watch with updates, delivering fresh new features, and offering support until October 2026. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eWhen it comes to hardware, the Pixel Watch 2 comes in just one size, with the 41mm model featuring a 1.2-inch AMOLED screen that can reach up to 1,000 nits of brightness. You also get a Qualcomm Snapdragon W5 processor that\u0026#39;s paired with 2GB of RAM and 32GB of internal storage. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThere are also a wealth of different sensors that can track your health and fitness metrics, and it also has an IP68 rating that protects it against dust and moisture. You really can\u0026#39;t go wrong with the Pixel Watch 2. It offers plenty of bang for your buck, especially at this newly discounted price, which makes it a no-brainer if you\u0026#39;ve been looking for a new smartwatch. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eGet it now while you still can, or just in case the Pixel Watch 2 isn\u0026#39;t to your liking, you can check out some other \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-amazon-prime-day-2025-deals/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esmartwatch deals we\u0026#39;ve covered during Prime Day\u003c/a\u003e. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
